      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add Skill Workshop proposals and skill research",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR moves Skill Workshop into the core skills subsystem and makes it the governed path for creating, revising, reviewing, and applying OpenClaw skill proposals.\n\nAgents now use `skill_workshop` for skill proposal work. Skill Research is kept as a separate internal layer for autonomous durable-instruction capture; when it detects reusable skill work, it queues a pending Workshop proposal instead of writing live skills directly.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Added durable Skill Workshop proposal storage under OpenClaw state, with `proposal.json`, `PROPOSAL.md`, support files, rollback metadata, and a rebuildable `proposals.json` manifest.\n- Added the `skill_workshop` agent tool for create, update, revise, list, inspect, apply, reject, and quarantine actions.\n- Added CLI commands under `openclaw skills workshop`.\n- Added Gateway proposal methods for list, inspect, create, update, apply, reject, and quarantine flows.\n- Added proposal support files under standard skill folders, with text-file validation, scanner checks, hash verification, stale-target detection, and guarded apply writes.\n- Added proposal revision support with versioned and dated proposal frontmatter.\n- Added Skill Research auto-capture as a separate internal layer that queues Workshop proposals when autonomous capture is enabled.\n- Added system prompt/tool catalog guidance so agents route skill creation and proposal lifecycle work through `skill_workshop`.\n- Removed the old Skill Workshop plugin package now that Workshop is core skills functionality.\n- Added docs and changelog entries for the proposal lifecycle.\n\n## Behavior\n\n- Generated skills are pending proposals by default.\n- Active skills are not overwritten silently.\n- Apply is workspace-scoped and checks stale target state before writing.\n- Update proposals preserve target baselines and mark stale when live skill/support files change.\n- Support files are validated, scanned, hash-checked, and rejected when unsafe or non-text.\n- Apply writes rollback metadata and uses guarded writes to avoid partial or clobbering publishes.\n- Reject and quarantine only operate on pending proposals.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- AWS Crabbox `cbx_d2a8fac69de8`:\n  `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tools/skill-workshop-tool.test.ts src/skills/research/autocapture.test.ts src/agents/harness/agent-end-side-effects.test.ts src/agents/agent-tools.before-tool-call.embedded-mode.test.ts src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts src/agents/tool-catalog.test.ts src/agents/agent-tools.create-openclaw-coding-tools.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt-tool-construction-plan.test.ts packages/gateway-protocol/src/schema/agents-models-skills.test.ts src/skills/workshop/service.test.ts`\n- AWS Crabbox `cbx_d2a8fac69de8`:\n  `pnpm check:changed -- <changed paths>`\n",
